    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided financial text, here is the definition, reconciliation, and formula for **Segment Adjusted EBITDA**.\n\n### **1. Definition**\n**Segment Adjusted EBITDA** is a non-GAAP financial measure defined as a segment's **income (loss) from operations** (the most directly comparable GAAP measure), excluding the following non-cash and non-recurring items:\n- (i) Depreciation and amortization\n- (ii) Share-based compensation\n- (iii) Restructuring charges\n- (iv) Impairment\n\nIt is used by management and investors as a key performance measure to assess the underlying financial performance of each business segment.\n\n### **2. Reconciliation from Loss from Operations & Explicit Formula**\nThe formula is explicitly stated and demonstrated in the reconciliation tables. The calculation for a given segment is:\n\n**Segment Adjusted EBITDA = Segment Income (Loss) from Operations + Depreciation & Amortization + Share-based Compensation + Restructuring Charges + Impairment**\n\n**Example Reconciliation (from the table for Q1 2026):**\n\n| (in millions) | **Space** | **Connectivity** | **AI** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Income (loss) from operations (GAAP)** | **$(662)** | **$1,188** | **$(2,469)** |\n| **Add:** | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 166 | 783 | 1,493 |\n| Share-based compensation | 145 | 116 | 378 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | (11) |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA (Non-GAAP)** | **$(351)** | **$2,087** | **$(609)** |\n\n### **3. Key Distinction: Segment vs. Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA**\n- **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:** Starts at the **segment operating income/loss level** and adds back only the four items listed above. It measures the profitability of each reportable segment (Space, Connectivity, AI).\n- **Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA:** Starts at the **consolidated net income/loss** level and adds back a broader set of items, including: Depreciation & Amortization, Share-based Compensation, Restructuring Charges, **Impairment, Interest Expense, Interest Income, Other Income/Expense, and Provision for Income Taxes.**\n\n**In summary, the explicit formula for Segment Adjusted EBITDA is a direct addition of four specific non-cash/non-recurring expenses back to a segment's GAAP operating profit (or loss).**",
